The President has declared a major disaster in the State of Nevada due to severe winter storms, flooding, and mudslides that occurred from January 5 to January 14, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Rosalyn L. Cole has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations in the future. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.